        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1826226643" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11543907860103830583"><i>A true page turner. </i><br/><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1452043013ra/17638498.gif' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>I received this book just yesterday. Picked it up in the morning and stopped not until I was at the last pages and my eyes got blood-shot!<br/><br/>The Four Patriots is the story of four young and enthusiastic people who want to bring major changes in India through improving the Indian politics. <br/><br/>It is hard to believe that The Four Patriots is the debut novel by the author. His characters are well articulated, sensible and more than that they look for their country&apos;s progress above all.</span>
  <span id="freeText11543907860103830583" style="display:none"><i>A true page turner. </i><br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1452043013ra/17638498.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>I received this book just yesterday. Picked it up in the morning and stopped not until I was at the last pages and my eyes got blood-shot!<br><br>The Four Patriots is the story of four young and enthusiastic people who want to bring major changes in India through improving the Indian politics. <br><br>It is hard to believe that The Four Patriots is the debut novel by the author. His characters are well articulated, sensible and more than that they look for their country's progress above all.<br><br>This quality and theme of this one, has impressed and surprised me.<br><br>I'm already astonished seeing the optimism The Four Patriots radiated. <br>The ideas provided by the author for the development of the country are sure unique and I congratulate him for coming up with those ideas and fabricating them beautifully.<br><br>In collaborating politics and the personal life of these four patriots,<a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/1684399.Sumit_Agarwal" title="Sumit Agarwal" rel="nofollow noopener">Sumit Agarwal</a> has definitely done a fabulous job. <br>I hope this book reaches to many young generation of India.<br><br>A Hindi translation of this book, would be the best thing that can happen to Hindi readers. <br><br>I would not have been reading a political fiction, had it not been for an exciting cover and blurb as this one. <br><br><i>At the end of the day, I'm glad to have picked up this book.</i><br><br><i>So would you be too. </i></span>
